==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Canis
<hw>Ca"nis</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧"n⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Canes</plw> <pr>(-n⟦emac⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.,
a dog.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of carnivorous mammals, of
the family <fam>Canid⟦ae⟧</fam>, including the dogs and
wolves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>\'d8Canis major</b></col> <ety>[L., larger dog]</ety>,
<cd>a constellation to the southeast of Orion, containing Sirius or the
Dog Star.</cd> -- <col><b>\'d8Canis minor</b></col> <ety>[L., smaller
dog]</ety>, <cd>a constellation to the east of Orion, containing
Procyon, a star of the first magnitude.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

